<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
Drangband, <p>
a module that is less ambitious than <a class="nonexistent" href="./ZoneBand">ZoneBand</a>, but more thought over. 
</p>
<p>
The premise is basically that Dragons are creatures that have merged their multiverse copies into one. They can take any shape but prefer the shape of a dragon, they often wander through the vast multiverse but have created their own home, the Dragon Tower.  
</p>
<p>
I am writing and reading some stuff about Shamans/Magic/Miracles/Myths in order to try to find some stuff I have not encountered yet in other fantasy. 
</p>
<p>
Throughout the game the player should find scrolls &amp; parchments that will help to understand the setting. 
</p>

    <ul>

    <li>
<p>
 <a href="./Modules_2fDrangBand_2fDrangBand_2fIntroMulti">/DrangBand/IntroMulti</a> : 'An introduction to multiverses' by Lord Maxartel. 
</p>
</li>
    <li>
<p>
 <a href="./Modules_2fDrangBand_2fDrangBand_2fMultiSing">/DrangBand/MultiSing</a> : 'On multiverse singularities' by Lord Maxartel. 
</p>
</li>

    </ul>


