<h3 id="head-ff11f0da0a4cd245270f188d8a7299b4084d0328">Chatter</h3>
<p>
<a href="./FeathinSilyar">FeathinSilyar</a>:  The name DrAngband is already used by a current variant of Angband, hosted at Thangorodrim.  It'd be rather confusing to have a ToME module named exactly the same as an Angband variant, so unless you are the maintainer of DrAngband I'd suggest switching the name slightly. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: I suggest more originality in names.  Don't clone DG's ToME style naming (Yes, I did so once.. but deliberately silly in a deliberately silly module).  Don't pick a word or a few random letters and slap 'band' on the end.  Real names for real modules! 
</p>

    <ul>

 <strong><a href="./RavenRed">RavenRed</a></strong> &lt;chants&gt;: Bring back ToMK, bring back ToMK...  
    </ul>


<p>
<strong><a href="./TheKonijn">TheKonijn</a></strong>: Ok, <a class="nonexistent" href="./DrangBand">DrangBand</a> is a name that exists since a while and that follows a traditional naming style from way before <a href="./DarkGod">DarkGod</a>. This module started out of frustration with the original Drangband which is basically FOOBAR now. So I think Drangband should be fine. 
</p>
